The paper deals with image processing and denoising, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method proposed involves matrix rank minimization, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of principle component analysis (PCA) and singular value decomposition (SVD) also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the choice of threshold parameter and estimation of PSNR values, which are topics in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
